<section id="usage-model">
    <h3>
        <i class="fas fa-database fa-lg"></i> 
        Model
    </h3>

    <header class="head">
        <p>
            For the Model naming, 
            you need to use the same name than each table...
        </p>
        <p>
            You can choose, 
            the Model path & the Model suffix, 
            in the parameters.
        </p>
        <p>
            For example (without any changes to the Model constants),
            if you have a table named Pizza, 
            you should have a Model named PizzaModel.php
        </p>
    </header>

    <i class="fas fa-minus fa-lg mar-top-md" 
        aria-hidden="true"></i>

    <ul>
        <li>
            <p>
                To use the Pam CRUD model, 
                simply add this use to each of your models :
            </p>
            <code>use Pam\Model\MainModel;</code>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>Then you can extends the class to the MainModel :</p>
            <code>extends MainModel</code>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p class="color-secondary font-bold">
                Now you can access to all CRUD methods of the MainModel !
            </p>
            <a class="button-secondary"
                href="https://github.com/philippebeck/pam.net/tree/master/src/Model/UserModel.php"
                title="See the Code">
                Simple Model Example
            </a>
        </li>
    </ul>

    <i class="fas fa-minus fa-lg mar-top-md" 
        aria-hidden="true"></i>

    <ul>
        <li>
            <p>
                If you need a specific query, 
                just create a method to add it :
            </p>
            <code>$query = "SELECT * FROM Table..."</code>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>Then you should return the query with one of the methods to the PdoDb.php file like this :</p>
            <code>return $this->database->getAllData($query);</code>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p class="color-secondary font-bold">
                Now you can use both Pam Model methods & personalized Model methods !
            </p>
            <a class="button-secondary"
                href="https://github.com/philippebeck/pam.net/tree/master/src/Model/PropertyModel.php"
                title="See the Code">
                Model Example with Personalized Query
            </a>
        </li>
    </ul>
</section>
